        <bioghist id="ref1">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Rackstraw Downes (1939-), a landscape painter and author in New York City, edited and wrote the introduction to
                <emph render="italic"> Fairfield Porter: Art In It's Own Terms: Selected Criticism 1935-1975</emph>. Born in Kent, England, Downes received a B.A. in English literature from Cambridge University in 1961 and earned an M.F.A. from the Yale School of Arts in 1961. Downes was personally acquainted with Porter.</p>
            <p>Fairfield Porter (1907-1975), a painter, art critic and poet, resided in Southampton, New York. Porter was a strong advocate for figure painting. He wrote for 
                <emph render="italic">ArtNews</emph> and 
                <emph render="italic">The Nation</emph>, and eventually became art editor for 
                <emph render="italic">The Nation</emph>.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <accessrestrict id="ref2">
